@@TJvErrorControl
Summary
  A control that can display and optionally blink an image.
Description
  TJvErrorControl is the class used for the error icons created by an error provider. Do not create instances of
  TJvErrorControl yourself. TJvErrorControl instances are created and maintained by TJvErrorProvider as needed.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.BlinkCount
Summary
  Specifies the number of times the icon should blink.
Description
  Read BlinkCount to determine how many times the image is blinked by the control. Change BlinkCount to
  set the number of times the icon should be blinked. While a blink is in progress, this value is automatically
  decremented.

  The BlinkCount property is handled by the owning TJVErrorProvider and should not normally be altered unless
  you are writing your own error provider.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.CalcBoundsRect
Summary
  Calculates the size and location of the control.
Description
  CalcBoundsRect calculates the suggested size and location of the control.
  The calculation is based on the size and location of the associated <LINK Control, Control>,
  the size of the image used for the error icon as well as the value of the ImageAligment property.
Return value
  A TRect that defines the size and location where the control should be located. Note that this does not imply
  that the returned location is where the control is actually located. The returned values are in client rect and is directly
  assignment compatible with the <LINK TControl.BoundsRect, BoundsRect> property.
See Also
  <LINK TControl.BoundsRect, BoundsRect>, Control, ImageIndex, ImageAlignment, Imagelist
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.Control
Summary
  Specifies the control this error icon is acting on.
Description
  Read Control to determine what control this error icon is acting upon. Change Control to make
  the error icon act on another control. The size and location of the error icon is automatically
  adjusted depending on the location of Control, the value of ImageAlignment as well as the size
  of the image(s) in the Imagelist.
See Also
  Control, ImageAlignment, Imagelist
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.DrawImage
Summary
  Method that draws the error icon.
Description
  DrawImage is called by the error rpovider to draw the error icon as appropriate. Override this method
  in descendant classes to draw the icon differently.
  the error
Parameters
  Erase - set to false if the icon should be visible, false otherwise
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.Error
Summary
  Specifies the error message to display.
Description
  Use Error to set the message to display in the control. The error is displayed in a hint window
  when the user moves the mouse over the icon. Normally, Error is set by the error provider that
  created the control.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.ImageAlignment
Summary
  Specifies where the error icon should be located.
Description
  Read ImageAlignment to determine where the error icon is located on the form. The value of
  ImageAlignment is relative to the Control it is assoicated with. Change ImageAlignment to
  move the error icon to another location.
See Also
  Control
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.ImageIndex
Summary
  Specifies the image to display in the control.
Description
  ImageIndex is the index of the image in Imagelist to display on the control. Set ImageIndex to -1 to
  not show any icon. Normally, this property is maintained by the error provider that created the control.
See Also
  Imagelist
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.Imagelist
Summary
  Specifies the image list used to display images in the control.
Description
  Use Imagelist to specify where the control retrieves it's icons. In combination with ImageIndex
See Also
  ImageIndex
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorControl.ImagePadding
Summary
  Specifies the padding around the images.
Description
  Use ImagePadding to make minor adjustments to the location of the image within the control. If ImagePadding
  is 0 or less, the image is centered within the control. The ImagePadding value is expressed in pixels.
See Also
  ImageAlignment
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment
<TITLE TJvErrorImageAlignment type>
Summary
  Controls where an error icon is displayed.
Description
  TJvErrorImageAlignment is the type used by the ImageAlignment porperty of error providers and
  indicates where an error image should be placed in relation to the control it is assoicated with.
  Possible values for this type are:
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment.eiaBottomLeft
  display the error image on the controls left side aligned to the bottom edge of the control
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment.eiaBottomRight
  display the error image on the controls right side aligned to the bottom edge of the control
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment.eiaMiddleLeft
  display the error image on the controls left side aligned to the middle of the control
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment.eiaMiddleRight
  display the error image on the controls right side aligned to the middle of the control
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment.eiaTopLeft
  display the error image on the controlsleft side aligned to the top edge of the control
@@TJvErrorImageAlignment.eiaTopRight
  display the error image on the controls right side aligned to the top edge of the control
